rounds.subjective: Patient reports chest pain 6/10, described as crushing, radiating to left arm. Shortness of breath on exertion.
rounds.objective: HR 102 bpm, BP 150/95, O2 sat 96% on 2L NC. EKG shows ST elevation in leads II, III, aVF. Troponin elevated at 2.5.
rounds.assessment: Acute inferior STEMI, cardiogenic shock risk. Requires urgent cardiac catheterization.
rounds.plan: Emergent cardiac cath, dual antiplatelet therapy, heparin protocol. Monitor cardiac enzymes q6h. Cardiology consult.

rounds.subjective: Patient reports palpitations and dizziness for 2 days. Denies chest pain but feels weak and fatigued.
rounds.objective: HR irregular 45-120 bpm, BP 110/70. EKG shows atrial fibrillation with RVR. Echo shows EF 35%, mild mitral regurgitation.
rounds.assessment: New onset atrial fibrillation with rapid ventricular response. Systolic heart failure, likely ischemic cardiomyopathy.
rounds.plan: Rate control with metoprolol, anticoagulation with warfarin. ACE inhibitor for heart failure. Cardiology follow-up in 1 week.

rounds.subjective: Patient reports severe shortness of breath, orthopnea, and bilateral lower extremity swelling for 1 week.
rounds.objective: HR 98 bpm, BP 160/100, RR 24, O2 sat 88% on room air. JVD present, bilateral crackles, 3+ pitting edema to knees.
rounds.assessment: Acute decompensated heart failure, NYHA Class IV. Possible acute on chronic systolic dysfunction.
rounds.plan: IV furosemide 40mg BID, strict I/O monitoring. Daily weights. Echo and BNP ordered. Consider ACE inhibitor when stable.

rounds.subjective: Complains of shortness of breath, worse with exertion.
rounds.objective: No signs of infection, surgical site clean and dry.
rounds.assessment: Improving UTI, continue antibiotics, monitor intake/output.
rounds.plan: Check iron studies, consider hematology consult if no improvement.
